Rating: 3
3.5 forks. Wonderful. I made a few variations, based on what I had on hand, my limitations as a baker, and other reviews: I used a frozen prefab pie crust (I'm not so good with the hand-made crusts), and I used 6 Granny Smith apples, which still produced enough filling to overflow and necessitate that I bake the pie on a sheet. Also, per another reviewer, I added some extra spices I had on hand to the crumb topping---nutmeg, mace, ginger, etc. Not imperative, but a nice touch. I bungled the baking temp, not noticing for quite some time that I was supposed to reduce the temp after the first ten minutes of baking. Though some of the apples' edges were dark brown by the time I corrected things, the pie was none the worse for wear. The pie was just lovely after it came out of the oven and cooled. Absolutely worth it. But the next day the leftovers were even better; it's true. And a slice of this pie is just a gorgeous photo op. The crumb topping makes this a very sweet pie, which I like, so people who don't have such a sweet tooth probably could cut back on the filling sugar significantly and still create a thing of beauty.

