Given the fourth of July celebrations last week, I thought an apple pie would be a nice treat for my American hubby. Now, he does like Irish style tarts (we don't do deep dish pies really) but I thought this recipe looked like a nice twist on a classic pie. I upped the amount of cinnamon, but that was the only change I made. Because this pie bakes in stages, make sure you have enough time to bake it...it's definitely not a throw it in and forget about it pie. That said, hubby devoured it, loved the kitsch factor of apple pie on fourth of July and has nominated it into his top two favorite recipes ever! Yep, of course the downside is that right now I have two more of the pies in the oven - one for home and one for his workmates. I heart this recipe!

